<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="sec-characteristic-of-ring" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Characteristic of a ring</title>
    
    
<p>In this section we define the <em>characteristic of a ring that contains a subfield</em>.</p>
<definition xml:id="def-characteristic-of-ring">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Let <m>f\colon\mathbb{Z}\to R</m> be a unique ring homomorphism. The kernel of <m>f</m> is generated by the unique positive integer <m>n</m>, <m>\ker f=\langle n\rangle</m>. The integer <m>n</m> is called the <em>characteristic</em> of <m>R</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
</definition>
</section>